<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Why Waverly's Newer Homes Still Need Egress Work</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>A lot of people assume that because their house is only 10 or 15 years old, the basement windows are already up to code. That's not always the case. Builders in Waverly often installed standard basement windows in unfinished lower levels since there was no bedroom there yet, which means the egress requirement never applied until someone decides to finish the space.</p><p>If you're converting a basement in one of Waverly's newer subdivisions into a bedroom, playroom with a closet, or guest suite, an egress window isn't optional. It's what allows a building inspector to sign off on the room as a legal sleeping space, and it's what gives your family a real way out if something goes wrong upstairs.</p><p>We size and place the window to match your framing plan, so it works with the layout you already have instead of forcing changes to your finishing project.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Serving Waverly and the US-6 Corridor</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>Waverly sits along US-6 northeast of Lincoln, and we work throughout the area, from the neighborhoods near the school campus to newer developments still being built out on the edges of town. Because Waverly is part of Lancaster County, egress window permits and inspections follow the same code requirements as Lincoln, so we already know what local inspectors expect to see.</p><p>Our crews are familiar with the soil and drainage conditions typical of this part of the county, which matters when we're setting a window well and making sure water moves away from your foundation instead of pooling against it.</p><p>Whether you're close to downtown Waverly or out toward the edge of the growth boundary, we bring the same process and the same <a href="/egress-window-cost/">written estimate</a> to every job.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Planning a Basement Bedroom in Waverly</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>Many of our Waverly calls come from families who bought a home with an unfinished basement expecting to grow into it. As kids get older or a commuter needs a home office, that basement becomes the next bedroom, and the egress window becomes the first thing on the checklist.</p><p>We recommend getting the egress window installed early in your finishing project, before drywall and flooring go in, since the cut-in work is dusty and easier to manage when the space is still open. That also lets your framing and window placement work together instead of you having to design around an opening later.</p><p>Call us before you finalize your basement plans and we'll walk the space with you, free of charge.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:72px 24px;background:#EAF5FB;">
